Chelsea Wins 2-0 at Copenhagen in Champions League; Lyon, Madrid Draw 1-1

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-02-22T21:40:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-22/chelsea-wins-2-0-at-copenhagen-in-champions-league-lyon-madrid-draw-1-1.html
Chelsea defeated FC Copenhagen 2-0
in their opening Champions League round of 16 game, while Lyon
tied 1-1 with Real  Madrid .    Nicolas Anelka  scored once in each half as Chelsea won in  Denmark . Bafetimbi Gomis’s goal in the 83rd minute gave Lyon the
home draw with nine-time champion Real Madrid. Karim Benzema got
Madrid’s goal.  Real Madrid and Chelsea will host the return matches in the
two-game series on March 16.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  